'' Langham dined with his people that night , Clay and MacWilliams having promised to follow him up the hill later . 
It was a night of much moment to them all , and the two men ate their dinner in silence , each considering what the coming of the strangers might mean to him . 
As he was leaving the room MacWilliams stopped and hovered uncertainly in the doorway . 
Are you going to get yourself into a dress suit to night ? '' he asked . 
Clay said that he thought he would he wanted to feel quite clean once more . 
